# Copy to `backend/.env` (gitignored). The dev script (`pnpm dev`) reads it
# via Node's --env-file flag — see backend/package.json scripts.

# REQUIRED — must be at least 32 bytes (hex strings work). Generate with:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(48).toString('hex'))"
JWT_SECRET=replace-me-with-32-or-more-bytes

# OPTIONAL — Tripo prompt-to-mesh. Both must be set together OR both omitted;
# TRIPO_ENABLED=true without TRIPO_API_KEY hard-fails at server startup.
# Without these, /api/generate slider mode (procedural shapes) still works;
# prompt mode (Forge "generate base car") rejects with 400 tripo_disabled.
# TRIPO_ENABLED=true
# TRIPO_API_KEY=...

# OPTIONAL — Tripo SUI fee config (D-034). Treasury (collects the fee) and fee
# amount in MIST both default in code (treasury = deployer, fee = 20 SUI testnet
# anti-abuse gate). MUST match the FE constant in modelTxBuilders.ts.
# TRIPO_FEE_TREASURY=0x...
# TRIPO_FEE_MIST=20000000000
# D-089 (audit B-4): the OPERATOR identity allowed the self-pay verifier bypass —
# the deployer who runs /create against their own treasury. Defaults to the
# deployer. ⚠️ If you ever set TRIPO_FEE_TREASURY to an address that is ALSO a
# real user wallet (shared/multisig/sponsor), you MUST set TRIPO_FEE_OPERATOR
# explicitly to the deployer so that user does NOT get free generations.
# TRIPO_FEE_OPERATOR=0x...

# OPTIONAL — MemWal "Riff Copilot" memory layer (D-080). When unset, the memory
# features are inert (recall returns nothing; /create is unaffected). Provision
# with backend/scripts/memwal-spike.ts. The delegate key acts across ALL
# namespaces of the account → SERVER-SIDE ONLY. NEVER prefix with VITE_ or add
# to any frontend env (the repo has a documented VITE_ key-confusion gotcha).
# Testnet relayer; default is https://relayer.dev.memwal.ai if MEMWAL_SERVER_URL unset.
# MEMWAL_SERVER_URL=https://relayer.dev.memwal.ai
# MEMWAL_ACCOUNT_ID=0x...
# MEMWAL_DELEGATE_KEY=<ed25519 hex>
# Recall relevance ceiling (cosine distance): results at/above this are dropped,
# so junk/vague queries don't surface the whole pool. Default 0.66 (probe-tuned:
# descriptive prompts ≤~0.62; junk words like "penis" sit ~0.71, overlapping
# bare "car" — a single threshold can't be perfect, see memory.ts). Lower =
# stricter (fewer, more-relevant results); higher = looser.
# MEMORY_MAX_DISTANCE=0.66

# OPTIONAL — L2 "Riff Copilot" conversational prompt-authoring (D-081). When unset,
# the copilot is INERT: the /api/copilot route reports {available:false} and the
# frontend shows a VISIBLE, disabled "AI unavailable" state (D-084 — never hidden at
# runtime; only the build-time VITE_COPILOT_ENABLED flag hides the feature). /create
# still works (L0/L1 + raw textarea). This is the Gemini API key, read by
# @ai-sdk/google. It is SERVER-SIDE ONLY — NEVER prefix with VITE_ or add to any
# frontend env (the browser never calls Gemini; all LLM calls go through the backend,
# mirroring the MemWal proxy). The LLM lives ONLY at the prompt-authoring seam;
# generation dispatch stays LLM-free (D-023). The SAME key also powers Upload
# Captioning (D-082): vision describe-on-upload via /api/caption. When unset, the
# "Describe with AI" button shows "AI UNAVAILABLE" (disabled, not hidden — D-084) and
# uploads mint with no caption. Both capabilities live or die with this one key.
# GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=...
# Optional model overrides; both default to gemini-2.5-flash (GA, fast, cheap,
# multimodal) in code. COPILOT_MODEL → L2 copilot; CAPTION_MODEL → upload captioning.
# COPILOT_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
# CAPTION_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# ── Third-party AI degradation UX (D-083) ────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠️ SECURITY: GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY and TRIPO_API_KEY are SERVER-SIDE ONLY.
# NEVER prefix either with VITE_ or copy them into frontend/.env — that ships the
# operator's paid key to every browser (the repo has a documented VITE_ key gotcha).
#
# Durable quota store (node:sqlite, D-083). Single long-running instance + a
# persistent VOLUME mounted at this path's directory (the dir is auto-created).
# Holds the cached Tripo balance + per-day Gemini usage counters + cooldowns so
# they survive restart/redeploy. Default (local dev): ./data/quota.db (gitignored).
# TUSK_DB_PATH=./data/quota.db
#
# Tripo generate pre-flight (R1): minimum spendable credits to allow a generation
# BEFORE charging the SUI fee. Conservative default 120 in code (exact Turbo-v1.0 +
# mesh_segmentation cost is unpublished, ~100–110cr/chain). CALIBRATE post-deploy:
# run one real two-step generation and diff the Tripo `balance`, then size this for
# expected concurrency (per-chain-cost × concurrency + buffer).
# TRIPO_PREFLIGHT_MIN_CREDITS=120
#
# Tripo balance poll cadence (ms); default 60000 in code. Drives the pre-flight's
# staleness TTL (≈ 2.5×): a cache older than that forces a live re-query, covering
# cold start AND a silently-dead poller.
# TRIPO_BALANCE_POLL_MS=60000
#
# Gemini global operator daily budget (R9). Default OFF (unset) so nothing changes
# until configured — needs calibration against real Google quota. Set a number to cap.
# GEMINI_DAILY_BUDGET=2000
#
# Gemini per-address daily cap (R8) — defense-in-depth against multi-wallet budget
# bypass (the per-minute limiter is trivially reset by churning cheap zkLogin
# wallets). DEFAULT-ON at 50/day/address in code (generous; real users never hit
# it). Set to a blank/non-numeric value to disable.
# GEMINI_PER_ADDRESS_DAILY=50

# list_fork_collections GraphQL enumeration endpoint (plan-2026-06-19-001).
# Defaults to testnet when unset; set the mainnet endpoint on the D-009 cutover.
# SUI_GRAPHQL_ENDPOINT=https://graphql.testnet.sui.io/graphql

# Frontend origin for MCP detailUrl click-through links (D-110).
# Defaults to https://tusk3d.store; MUST be the SPA host, not the backend host.
# PUBLIC_WEB_ORIGIN=https://tusk3d.store
